</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#8E236B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/utesarra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tesarra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/28/02 8:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=170.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Petition for Entrance</span><hr size=1> Tesarra glanced up quickly to check the silhouettes of the Koada'Dal near the harbor.  So far so good.  They seemed not to have noticed her attacks on the fringes of the Erolisi Sisterhood's encampment on the island.  They would surely wonder tomorrow who was responsible for the group of corpses piled upon the beach, but Tes would be long gone by then.<br>
<br>
With another glance up to check the opposite shore of the island for any sign of activity (she had narrowly escaped death at the hands of a pirate from that direction a few hours ago), she returned to the task of removing the Purity Belt from her latest victim.  The girl was much younger than Tesarra, but had been nearly her equal in combat.  If not for the melee skill of her bone servant, there was little doubt in Tesarra's mind who would be lying on the beach growing slowly colder.<br>
<br>
She placed the belt in her pack, taking a quick inventory as she did.  She had collected six now, two more than the Dread Overlord Pravdameer had requested for her Culling Quest, but scarcely enough to begin her revenge on the lightdwellers who had invaded her precious Nektulos Forest.  Tes allowed her rage to flare up momentarily, her eyes flickering in the night like bright embers.  Only for a moment did she allow herself to luxuriate in the building fire of anger and Hatred that came from deep within her soul.<br>
<br>
Just as quickly, her eyes resumed their normal calm violet hue as she banked the embers of the fire within.  Her enemies would think her an anomaly.  Before them would stand a Tier'Dal seemingly without the burning Hatred that drove her kin.  She would win their confidence, even their friendship with her poise and quick wit.  Then, oh then...  A hideous grin crept across Tesarra's lips as she carved a few choice portions of meat from the young Koada'Dal bodies before her, wrapping them carefully in packets of their own skin with herbs to preserve them until they could be cooked.<br>
<br>
The wolfish grin still lingered as she invoked the magicks that would transport her back home to Nektulos Forest.<br>
<br>
<br>
Tesarra the Necromancer<br>
